body:
It has come to my attention that a new league team has been made, team Pandacute, this team is all female. Though I believe it was only made to make money who knows. The leader of this team is supposedly a master rank player. For years now people have asked why there are barely any female players in League and in professional. Well think of it this way, say a girl comes into a game with the name like ShootThemDownGirl or PuppyAnCatChick, most of the time you will get &quot;Are you a girl?&quot; &quot;Look a gamer girl&quot; &quot;How old are you?&quot; along with name calling, sexism, and many other hurtful things. By the end of it usually you get upset and the people who said those things then try to add you.  It can get tiring and just makes you want to stop playing. League is a very toxic and hateful game because of its community, if you were to go onto rank right now and play a match, you will find your team screaming, cursing, and hating on each other. So for some, they just choose to not play rank and not play League. Riot has tried over the years to calm down the toxic and hate but it still happens. If you ever want females to get into League more, we all have to calm down, start respecting each other and treat others like how you would want to be treated. If someone is being treated badly don&#039;t sit there and watch, defend them, it doesn&#039;t matter if they are on your enemy team or not, no one should be treated badly. For such a toxic community this is a big step but in the future, maybe one day, we may see kinder people and more women. This is my own thoughts and opinions, if you would like to share yours then please leave a comment and try to keep it positive. Thank you.
~KittyLovesPoros
